# Test Report Management Endpoints

## 1. Create Report (Admin/Doctor)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/reports
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appointmentId": "APPOINTMENT_ID_HERE",
  "patientId": "PATIENT_ID_HERE",
  "doctorId": "DOCTOR_ID_HERE",
  "diagnosis": "Hypertension",
  "prescription": "Amlodipine 5mg once daily for 30 days",
  "labTests": [
    {
      "testName": "Blood Pressure",
      "result": "140/90 mmHg",
      "date": "2026-02-10"
    }
  ],
  "notes": "Patient advised to reduce salt intake and exercise regularly"
}

###

## 2. Get All Reports (with pagination)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/reports?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

###

## 3. Get Single Report
GET http://localhost:5000/api/reports/REPORT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

###

## 4. Update Report (Admin/Doctor)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/reports/REPORT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "diagnosis": "Hypertension - Stage 1",
  "prescription": "Amlodipine 5mg once daily, Aspirin 75mg once daily",
  "notes": "Follow-up in 2 weeks"
}

###

## 5. Delete Report (Admin Only)
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/reports/REPORT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

###

## 6. Download Report PDF
GET http://localhost:5000/api/reports/pdf/REPORT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

###
